The paper discusses the integration of architectural elements with a modern programming language, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The focus is on distributed, asynchronously communicating systems, which suggests a connection to distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of Java as an example for integration points towards programming languages (cs.PL). The mention of architectural description and design suggests a connection to architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the title mentions embedded systems, which suggests a connection to embedded systems (cs.EM).
